#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""End-to-end UI test: pizzeria ordering scenario through the React frontend.

Extension of ``skel-test-pizzeria-orders`` that drives a real browser
against the generated React app via Playwright. The scenario the test
proves:

    1. CLIENT logs into the web UI.
    2. CLIENT places a pizza order (browses catalog, selects pizzas).
    3. RESTAURANT logs in (separate superuser account on a separate tab).
    4. RESTAURANT approves the order with a wait-time + feedback.
    5. CLIENT (refreshes / re-navigates and) sees the wait time and
       feedback on the web UI.

Because the dev_skel React skeleton ships generic items-style UI, the
first iteration may not have the restaurant-approval / wait-time
screens the scenario needs. We ask ``./ai`` (per-service refactor
agent) to add them via the same iteration loop used in
``skel-test-pizza-reservation`` (sanitisers, missing-module shims,
selective baseline rollback). After ``./ai`` finishes, the runner
boots backend + frontend and exercises the flow with Playwright.

Exit codes mirror the other playbook runners (0 ok, 1 fail, 2 setup
skip).
"""

